<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-25T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-25T04:00:00-05:00" n="1409" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1409">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/11–2549: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Macdonald</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-25T17:00:00+08:00">November
                                    25, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 25—7:01 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>745. ReDeptel 483, November 23, 7 p. m. Oral warnings continue as
                            opportunity permits. Americans’ reaction negative. No immediate
                            departures expected.</p>
                        <p>American official reaction to Deptel 446 similar except in case of those
                            previously caught on mainland none of whom should in our opinion remain
                            here for second “liberation”. Does Department contemplate replacing
                            female employees here?</p>
                        <p>Sent Department 745, repeated Manila unnumbered.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Macdonald</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>